# Project Skills Directory

Workflow skills for this Ansible collection live in **`skills/`** at the repository root.

## Format

Skills use **`.mdc`** (Markdown + YAML frontmatter), not plain `.md`. Frontmatter supports:

- `description` — when to use the skill (shown in rule picker / agent discovery)
- `alwaysApply` — usually `false`; workflow skills are read on demand
- `globs` — optional file patterns that tie a skill to paths (for example `roles/dispatch/**`)

## Before Every Change

1. Follow `.cursor/rules/satellite-general.mdc` (always applied).
2. Read **`skills/fqcn-standards.mdc`** when editing tasks, playbooks, templates, plugins, or role `meta/main.yml`.
3. When the user names a skill or the task matches a skill `description`, read **`skills/<skill-name>.mdc`** and follow it.

## Invocation Examples

- `Use add-object-type-end-to-end to add satellite_compute_resources support.`
- `Use extend-filetree-create-object-type for export of a new object type.`
- `Use extend-dispatch-object-type to wire dispatch for satellite_subnets.`

## Skill Catalog

See `skills/README.md` for the full list grouped by role (export, ingest, dispatch, domain workflows).

## Legacy Path

Skills were moved from `.cursor/skills/` to `skills/` so they are editor-agnostic and shareable outside Cursor. Do not recreate skills under `.cursor/skills/`.
